headline: Northern Trust (NasdaqGS:NTRS) Proposes 7% Dividend Increase Pending Board Approval
summary: Northern Trust (NasdaqGS:NTRS) has proposed a 7% increase in its quarterly cash dividend, reflecting its intent to enhance shareholder returns. Over the last quarter, the company's stock price surged 30%. This upward trend aligns with its strong first-quarter earnings report, which showed significant rises in net interest income and net income, enhancing investor confidence. summary: Northern Trust is all set to release its fiscal second-quarter earnings later this month, and analysts project a double-digit earnings growth.
